      "writtenOn": "2019-03-15T02:11:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the line between FAILURE and INFRA_FAILURE is whether to blame the patch/commit or something else. From buildbucket perspective, build script (recipe) decides who to blame. From this perspective, a status TIMEOUT would be ambiguous: who is to blame?\n\nperhaps (who to blame) and (is it a timeout) are orthogonal. What use case do you want to cover by providing \"did it timeout\" bit? i.e. who will consume the bit?\n\nAnyway, if we need it, i think we could add `bool is_timeout` in StatusDetails.",
